# ğŸš€ Prometheus + Grafana â€” Kubernetes Monitoring

## Practical Work (Step-by-Step)

### ğŸŸ¢ Step 1: Launch New EC2 Server

* OS: Ubuntu 22.04 LTS, Type: t2.medium (2 vCPU, 4 GB RAM)
* Enable ports: 22(SSH), 6443(K8s API), 3000(Grafana), 9090(Prometheus)
  **Roman Urdu:** Naya server launch karte hain aur required ports open karte hain.

---

### ğŸŸ¢ Step 2: Update OS & Install Prerequisites

```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install -y apt-transport-https ca-certificates curl gnupg lsb-release software-properties-common
```

**Roman Urdu:** Server update kar rahe hain aur zaroori packages install kar rahe hain.

---

### ğŸŸ¢ Step 3: Install Docker

```bash
sudo apt install -y docker.io
sudo systemctl enable docker
sudo systemctl start docker
```

**Roman Urdu:** Docker install karke start aur enable kar rahe hain.

---

### ğŸŸ¢ Step 4: Install containerd & Configure

```bash
sudo apt install -y containerd
sudo mkdir -p /etc/containerd
containerd config default | sudo tee /etc/containerd/config.toml
sudo sed -i 's/SystemdCgroup = false/SystemdCgroup = true/' /etc/containerd/config.toml
sudo systemctl restart containerd
sudo systemctl enable containerd
```

**Roman Urdu:** Containerd install karte hain aur systemd cgroup enable karte hain.

---

### ğŸŸ¢ Step 5: Disable Swap & Load Modules

```bash
sudo swapoff -a
sudo sed -i '/ swap / s/^/#/' /etc/fstab

sudo modprobe overlay
sudo modprobe br_netfilter

cat <<EOF | sudo tee /etc/modules-load.d/k8s.conf
overlay
br_netfilter
EOF

cat <<EOF | sudo tee /etc/sysctl.d/k8s.conf
net.bridge.bridge-nf-call-ip6tables = 1
net.bridge.bridge-nf-call-iptables = 1
net.ipv4.ip_forward = 1
EOF

sudo sysctl --system
```

**Roman Urdu:** Swap disable karte hain aur Kubernetes ke required kernel modules load karte hain.

---

### ğŸŸ¢ Step 6: Install Kubernetes

```bash
sudo mkdir -p /etc/apt/keyrings
curl -fsSL https://pkgs.k8s.io/core:/stable:/v1.30/deb/Release.key | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes-apt-keyring.gpg

echo "deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes-apt-keyring.gpg] https://pkgs.k8s.io/core:/stable:/v1.30/deb/ /" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/kubernetes.list

sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y kubelet kubeadm kubectl
sudo apt-mark hold kubelet kubeadm kubectl
```

**Roman Urdu:** Kubernetes tools install karte hain aur update block kar dete hain.

---

### ğŸŸ¢ Step 7: Initialize Cluster with Calico CNI

```bash
sudo kubeadm init --pod-network-cidr=192.168.0.0/16
```

**Roman Urdu:** Cluster initialize karte hain aur output mein kubeconfig aur join command note karte hain.

---

### ğŸŸ¢ Step 8: Configure kubectl Access

```bash
mkdir -p $HOME/.kube
sudo cp -i /etc/kubernetes/admin.conf $HOME/.kube/config
sudo chown $(id -u):$(id -g) $HOME/.kube/config
```

**Roman Urdu:** Kubectl access setup karte hain apne user ke liye.

---

### ğŸŸ¢ Step 9: Install Calico Network Plugin

```bash
kubectl apply -f https://docs.projectcalico.org/manifests/calico.yaml
```

**Roman Urdu:** Network plugin apply karte hain cluster ke liye.

---

### ğŸŸ¢ Step 10: Install Helm

```bash
curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/helm/helm/main/scripts/get-helm-3 | bash
helm version
```

**Roman Urdu:** Helm install aur verify karte hain.

---

### ğŸŸ¢ Step 11: Install Prometheus + Grafana via Helm

#### 11.1 Add Helm Repo

```bash
helm repo add prometheus-community https://prometheus-community.github.io/helm-charts
helm repo update
```

**Roman Urdu:** Helm ko batate hain Prometheus repo se install karne ke liye.

#### 11.2 Remove Control Plane Taint

```bash
kubectl taint nodes --all node-role.kubernetes.io/control-plane-
```

**Roman Urdu:** Single node cluster pe regular pods allow karne ke liye taint remove karte hain.

#### 11.3 Create Namespace

```bash
kubectl create namespace monitoring
```

**Roman Urdu:** Monitoring ke liye alag namespace banate hain.

#### 11.4 Install Prometheus Stack

```bash
helm install prometheus-stack prometheus-community/kube-prometheus-stack \
  --namespace monitoring \
  --set prometheus.prometheusSpec.storageSpec.volumeClaimTemplate=null \
  --set alertmanager.alertmanagerSpec.storage.volumeClaimTemplate=null \
  --set grafana.persistence.enabled=false \
  --wait \
  --timeout 10m
```

**Roman Urdu:** Prometheus aur Grafana deploy karte hain error-free; persistence disable aur wait options ke sath.

---

### ğŸ” Step 12: Verify Pods

```bash
kubectl get pods -n monitoring
```

**Roman Urdu:** Check karein sab pods running hain ya nahi (prometheus, grafana, kube-state-metrics).

---

### ğŸŒ Step 13: Port Forward to Grafana

```bash
kubectl port-forward svc/prometheus-stack-grafana 3000:80 -n monitoring
```

**Access:** [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000)

**Login Info:**

```bash
kubectl get secret --namespace monitoring prometheus-stack-grafana -o jsonpath="{.data.admin-password}" | base64 -d
```

**Username:** admin
**Password:** from above command

**Roman Urdu:** Port forward se Grafana browser pe access karte hain.

---

### ğŸ’» Grafana Access via PuTTY Tunnel

1. Open PuTTY â†’ Hostname: `ubuntu@<EC2-IP>`
2. Connection â†’ SSH â†’ Auth â†’ Browse `.ppk` file
3. Connection â†’ SSH â†’ Tunnels â†’ Source: 3000, Destination: localhost:3000 â†’ Add
4. Save session â†’ Open â†’ Login
5. EC2 me run karein:

```bash
kubectl --namespace monitoring port-forward svc/prometheus-stack-grafana 3000:80
```

6. Browser: [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000)

**Roman Urdu:** Laptop ke localhost ko EC2 ke Grafana se connect karne ke liye tunnel banate hain.

---

### ğŸ” Prometheus Access via Tunnel

1. New tunnel: Source 9090 â†’ Destination 9090
2. Run EC2 me:

```bash
kubectl port-forward svc/prometheus-stack-kube-prom-prometheus 9090 -n monitoring
```

3. Browser: [http://localhost:9090](http://localhost:9090)

**Roman Urdu:** Prometheus dashboard bhi access karte hain same tarah.

